:R-HSA-74751  a             owl:NamedIndividual , obo:GO_0008150 ;
        rdfs:comment        "Autophosphorylation of the insulin receptor triggers a series of signalling events, mediated by SHC or IRS, and resulting in activation of the Ras/RAF and MAP kinase cascades. A second effect of the autophosphorylation of the insulin receptor is its internalisation into an endosome, which downregulates its signalling activity." ;
